'''Kraul Mountains''' is a chain of [[mountain]]s and [[nunatak]]s that trend northeastward from [[Veststraumen Glacier]] for approximately {{convert|70|mi|km}} in western [[Queen Maud Land]]. They were discovered by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938â1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], and named for Capt. Otto Kraul, ice pilot of the expedition.

